Java

The CIC Java code format is based on this document and embodied by the following Eclipse preferences (set using the Window > Preferences menu item):

On the General > Editors > Text Editors tab:
Check the "Insert spaces for tabs" box.
"Show print margin" is often helpful. Set the print margin column to 132.

On the General > Workspace tab:
Under "New text file line delimiter", select "Other", then select "Unix".
On the Ant > Editor > Formatter tab:
Turn off the "Use tab character instead of spaces" box.

On the Java > Code Style > Clean Up tab:
Click the Import... button and import JavaCodeCleanup.xml

On the Java > Code Style > Code Templates tab:
Click the Import... button and import JavaCodeTemplates.xml
Check the "Automatically add comments for new methods and types" box

On the Java > Code Style > Formatter tab:
Click the Import... button and import JavaCodeFormat.xml

On the Java > Editor > Save Actions tab:
Check "Perform the selected actions on save".
Check "Format source code".
Check "Additional actions".
Click the Configure... button.

On the "Code Organizing" tab:
Check "Remove trailing whitespace".
Uncheck "Correct indentation" for Eclipse luna. (On Eclipse Luna, this setting may have to be unchecked, or abnormal indentation of source code may occur)

On the "Code Style" tab:
Check "Use blocks in if/while/for/do statements".
Check "Convert for loops to enhanced".
Under "Variable declarations", check "Parameter" and "Local variables".

On the "Member Accesses" tab:
Check "Use declaring class as qualifier".

On the "Unnecessary Code" tab:
Check "Remove unused imports".
Check "Remove unnecessary '$NON-NLS$' tags".
Click OK.

On the XML > XML Files > Editor tab:
Set "Line width" to 132.
Under "Format comments", uncheck "Join lines".
Select "Indent using spaces".
Set "Indentation size" to 4.
